- build_meta_tags
.jumbotron
  .pull-right.ruby-logo
    = render :partial => "ruby_logo"
  %h1 Nairuby Ruby Users Group
  %p 
  %p
    Welcome to Nairuby, a user group for
    = link_to "Ruby", "https://www.ruby-lang.org/"
    programmers based in
    = link_to "Nairobi, Kenya.", "http://goo.gl/AMspr8"
    We welcome all programmers of all levels, from beginner to advanced!

.alert.alert-danger
  %strong RubyConf Philippines 2015
  will be held on 27-28 March, 2015 at Boracay!
  = link_to "Visit the official site for more details.", "http://rubyconf.ph"

.row.front-columns

  .col-md-4
    %h2 Know the local scene
    %p 
      Want to know who uses Ruby in the Philippines? Connect with the community via:
    %ul.community-links
      %li
        = link_to "http://www.meetup.com/ruby-phil/" do
          %span.fa.fa-users
          Meetup.com
        (sign-up to receive notifications)
      %li
        = link_to "http://www.facebook.com/groups/phrug/", target: '_blank' do
          %span.fa.fa-facebook
          Facebook Group
      %li
        = link_to "https://twitter.com/NairubyKE", target: '_blank' do
          %span.fa.fa-twitter
          Twitter
      %li 
        = link_to "https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/nairuby", target: '_blank' do
          %span.fa.fa-envelope
          Google Group
      
  .col-md-4
    %h2 Join our meetups
    %p We hold meetups every third Thursday of the month. 
    %p There we talk about all things related to Ruby and Rails, network over pizza, and afterwards we go out for a drink.
    %p 
      Our next meetup is on
      %strong= next_meetup(@next_meetup)
    %p= link_to "Find out more about our events", events_url, :class => "btn btn-default btn-lg"
    
  .col-md-4
    %h2 Learn Ruby and Rails
    %p Want to learn Ruby and Rails but don't know which among the many online resources out there are actually good? 
    %p= link_to "We've got you covered.", learn_url, :class => "btn btn-default btn-lg"

